oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: George Morgan, Gary Van, and the Plainsmen Quartet
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Gibson, Curt; Grand Ole Opry (Radio program); Harry (Hap) Peebles Agency; Maphis, Joe, 1921-1986; Maphis, Rose Lee; Morgan, George, 1925-1975; Valli, Jean; Van, Gary;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A black and white negative advertising Grand Ole Opry stars George Morgan, Joe and Rose Lee Maphis, Curt Gibson, the Plainsmen Quartet, and Gary Van, available through the Harry (Hap) Peebles Agency. The negative features photographs of George Morgan, Joe and Rose Lee Maphis, the Plainsmen Quartet, and Gary Van. The portion of the negative that would have featured Joe and Rose Lee Maphis' name has been cut and is missing. The negative would have been used to create a corresponding printing plate.
